nmsL2ProtocolTunnelMIB.name: nmsL2ProtocolTunnelMIB
nmsL2ProtocolTunnelMIB.description: This MIB module is for layer 2 protocol tunneling configurations. Layer 2 protocol tunneling function allows separate user networks to be considered as a single LAN. These user networks are connected via a switched network, which is running L2PT, and transparently forwads the specified l2 protocol data units(PDUs) from one user network to another.

l2ptIntfTable.name: l2ptIntfTable
l2ptIntfTable.description: This table contains the L2 protocol tunnel configuration of interfaces. Currently supported L2 PDU type is STP.

l2ptIntfEntry.name: l2ptIntfEntry
l2ptIntfEntry.description: L2 protocol tunnel configuration of interfaces.

l2ptIntfStpTnl.name: l2ptIntfStpTnl
l2ptIntfStpTnl.description: Indicates if the tunneling of STP BPDUs is enabled on this interface.
